query.esql:
FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http"  AND user_agent.original is not null
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS COUNT_DISTINCT(event.id)
| RENAME `COUNT_DISTINCT(event.id)` AS `Distinct Connections`
| KEEP `Distinct Connections`

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http"  AND user_agent.original is not null
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS COUNT_DISTINCT(event.id)
| RENAME `COUNT_DISTINCT(event.id)` AS `Distinct Connections`
| KEEP `Distinct Connections`

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND user_agent.original is not null
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(http.response.body.bytes) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id
| STATS AVG(`VALUES(http.response.body.bytes)`)
| EVAL `Average Body Length` = ROUND(`AVG(``VALUES(http.response.body.bytes)``)`)
| KEEP `Average Body Length`

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND user_agent.original is not null
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(http.response.body.bytes) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id
| STATS AVG(`VALUES(http.response.body.bytes)`)
| EVAL `Average Body Length` = ROUND(`AVG(``VALUES(http.response.body.bytes)``)`)
| KEEP `Average Body Length`

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND user_agent.original is not null
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(user_agent.original_length) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id
| STATS AVG(`VALUES(user_agent.original_length)`)
| EVAL `Average User Agent Length` = ROUND(`AVG(``VALUES(user_agent.original_length)``)`) 
| KEEP `Average User Agent Length`

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND user_agent.original is not null
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(user_agent.original_length) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id
| STATS AVG(`VALUES(user_agent.original_length)`)
| EVAL `Average User Agent Length` = ROUND(`AVG(``VALUES(user_agent.original_length)``)`) 
| KEEP `Average User Agent Length`

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND user_agent.original is not null AND http.response.status_name IS NOT NULL
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(http.response.status_name) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id 
| STATS COUNT() by `VALUES(http.response.status_name)` 
| RENAME `VALUES(http.response.status_name)` as `Status Message`, `COUNT()` as Count
| SORT Count DESC
| LIMIT 10 
| KEEP `Status Message`, Count

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND user_agent.original is not null AND http.response.status_name IS NOT NULL
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(http.response.status_name) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id 
| STATS COUNT() by `VALUES(http.response.status_name)` 
| RENAME `VALUES(http.response.status_name)` as `Status Message`, `COUNT()` as Count
| SORT Count DESC
| LIMIT 10 
| KEEP `Status Message`, Count

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND dest_host is not null
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(dest_host) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id 
| STATS COUNT() by `VALUES(dest_host)` 
| RENAME `VALUES(dest_host)` as `Host Header`, `COUNT()` as Count
| SORT Count desc
| LIMIT 10
| KEEP `Host Header`, Count

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND dest_host is not null
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(dest_host) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id 
| STATS COUNT() by `VALUES(dest_host)`

panelsJSON.title: Host Breakdown By HTTP Method [Logs Corelight]

query.esql:
FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND dest_host is not null AND http.response.status_code IS NOT NULL
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(dest_host), VALUES(http.response.status_code), VALUES(http.response.status_name) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id 
| STATS COUNT() by `VALUES(dest_host)`, `VALUES(http.response.status_code)` , `VALUES(http.response.status_name)`  
| RENAME `VALUES(dest_host)` as `Host Header`, `VALUES(http.response.status_code)` as `Status Code`, `VALUES(http.response.status_name)` as `Status Message`, `COUNT()` as Count
| SORT Count desc
| KEEP `Host Header`, `Status Code`, `Status Message`, Count

FROM logs-corelight.http*
| WHERE event.dataset == "http" AND dest_host is not null AND http.response.status_code IS NOT NULL
| LIMIT 10000
| STATS VALUES(dest_host), VALUES(http.response.status_code), VALUES(http.response.status_name) by source.ip, destination.ip, event.id 
| STATS COUNT() by `VALUES(dest_host)`, `VALUES(http.response.status_code)` , `VALUES(http.response.status_name)`  
| RENAME `VALUES(dest_host)` as `Host Header`, `VALUES(http.response.status_code)` as `Status Code`, `VALUES(http.response.status_name)` as `Status Message`, `COUNT()` as Count
| SORT Count desc
| KEEP `Host Header`, `Status Code`, `Status Message`, Count
